ASSIGNMENT 1: GIT — STEP BY STEP PROCESS
🔹 Step 1: Open VS Code
Open VS Code
Click File → Open Folder
Create a new folder named LibrarySystem
Open that folder
🔹 Step 2: Open Terminal
In VS Code:
Click Terminal → New Terminal
Terminal opens at bottom
🔹 Step 3: Initialize Git

👉 Type in terminal:

git init
🔹 Step 4: Create Python File

👉 In terminal:

touch app.py

👉 Open app.py and type:

print("Hello Library")
🔹 Step 5: Add and Commit

👉 In terminal:

git add app.py
git commit -m "first commit"
🔹 Step 6: Modify and Track Changes

👉 Change code in app.py

👉 Then type:

git diff
git add app.py
git commit -m "updated"
git log
🔹 Step 7: Create Branch

👉 In terminal:

git branch feature
git checkout feature

👉 Modify file → then:

git add .
git commit -m "feature added"
git checkout main
🔹 Step 8: Merge Branch

👉 In terminal:

git merge feature
🔹 Step 9: Push to GitHub

👉 Go to GitHub (browser) → Create new repository

👉 Then in terminal:

git remote add origin <repository-url>
git push -u origin main
